Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Boil the @Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli{250%grams}, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain. Drizzle with @oil{} and gently stir to prevent it from sticking.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Fry the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%grams} and @Sliced Mushrooms{80%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

Stir through the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Pesto{32%grams}, @Peas{120%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{50%milliliter(s)}. Simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the ravioli to the pesto sauce. Stir gently to combine.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Serve the pasta in #bowls{}.

Enjoy!